Cinder-GTest
============
Google unit testing for Cinder

This block introduces macros for creating Cinder apps 
compatible with Google Test.

WINDOWS
============

Use Google's Test UI as a free test runner:
[http://code.google.com/p/gtest-gbar/](http://code.google.com/p/gtest-gbar/)

Or generate logs like so:

1) Create a folder to store your logs. For example, "c:\GoogleTest". 
2) Go to "My Computer", right click and go to "Properties". 
3) Go to "Advanced system settings" and open "Environment Variables". 
4) Click "New" under "System variables" and add the following: 
   a. Variable name: GTEST_OUTPUT 
   b. Variable Value: xml:c:\GoogleTest\